               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. BODKIN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">DAWSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-1534" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1534" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1534" type="surname" value="SYEDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1534" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY SYEDS</persName>
                  </hi>. My husband is a tobacconist, in Rotherhithe Wall. On 15th Aug., Saunders came for half an ounce of tobacco—he paid me with a very new shilling of the Queen's reign—I gave him change for it, and put it into my pocket—I had two old shillings there—a policeman came—I took the three shillings out of my pocket, and at once recognized this one pro<lb></lb>duced, which I had taken of Saunders—the other two were King William's—I gave it to the policeman—this is like the paper of tobacco I sold to Saunders.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-1535" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1535" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1535" type="surname" value="ANDERSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1535" type="given" value="ROBERT WILLIAM"></interp>ROBERT WILLIAM ANDERSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a fancy soap-maker, of Deptford.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184808210234"></xptr>
               <p>On 15th Aug., Saunders came and asked for half an ounce of bear's greases—he gave me a Victoria shilling—I gave him 10 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>. change, and he left an officer, came in directly, and I gave him the shilling—I had but one other which was Georce the Third's—the officer followed the prisoner—I followed the officer—I fell in with the two prisoners down a turning—they were greasing their hair and laughing—I told Saunders he came to my house just now to buy some bear's grease—he said, "Yes"—I told him he gave me a bad shilling—he said, "Did I"—I said, "You know you did"—he was going to put his hand into his left hand pocket to give me some money, and Jones said, "No, not that pocket"—he put his hand then into his right pocket, and gave me a good shilling—I then asked him for the 10 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and he gave it me from the same pocket lie took the good shilling from—I collared him, and called the officer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-1536" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1536" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1536" type="surname" value="WHITLAMB"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1536" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WHITLAMB</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, M</hi> 89). On 15th Aug. I went to Mrs. Symm's after Saunders came out—she gave me this shilling—I had seen the prisoners before together, and afterwards I followed them—Saunders went into Mr. Anderson's—Jones was about 100 yards off, apparently watching the door—Saunders came out, and I followed the two prisoners to Hughes' Fields—I saw them rubbing their hands on their heads—I took Saunders.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-1537" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1537" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1537" type="surname" value="WEST"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1537" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS WEST</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, M</hi> 249). I went into Mr. Anderson's shop—he gave me this shilling—I followed the prisoners—I afterwards saw Mr. Anderson with them—he called me—I took Jones, and found this tobacco in his pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-1538" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1538" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1538" type="surname" value="POWELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-1538" type="given" value="CALEB EDWARD"></interp>CALEB EDWARD POWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of coin to the Mint—these shillings are both counterfeit, and cast in the same mould.</p>
